Web Application for Book management

Homepage:
	Shows all books
	Can add a new book with a button that takes the user to a new form-page
		User is then sent back to the homepage
		
Book Element:
	Should be able to edit with an "edit" button by the book
		When "edit" is clicked, the user should be sent to a new form-page then sent back to home when "save" is clicked
	"Delete" button to delete a book
	
Token Management
	User authentication with JSON web tokens
	Log-in page with username and password
	Register new account
	After login, back-end generates a token (in local storage or cookie) and sends back to front end
		Use then for subsequent API request to the back end
	Implement tocken validation in the back-end

Quote Page:
	Show a list of 5 quotes that I like
	Should be able to add, delete, and edit the quotes
	Button that switches between book view and quote view
	
Responsive Design Testing:
	Website smoothly adapts to screen size changes Ex: Tablets, computers, phones
	Navigation menus collapse into the responsive mobile menus or smaller screens
	Fields and buttons are approritaly sized across viewing platforms
	
Bootstrap and Font Awesome
	Use Bootstrap for the front end
	Awesome icons to visual elements of application
	Font Awesome icons are used and displayed correctly
	
Host application on a free platform such as Netlify or Vercel
Send code repo by GitHub link
		
